1️⃣ iOS Safari cannot process large base64 images

On mobile, this line is the biggest problem:

const base64 = canvas.toDataURL('image/jpeg', 0.9);


📱 iOS Safari often fails silently when:

Canvas resolution is large (1280×720 or higher)

JPEG quality is high (0.9)

Base64 string exceeds memory limit

➡️ Result:

Image looks like it captured

But Gemini / image API never receives a valid image

No visible crash

✅ Laptop browsers handle this fine
❌ Phones do not

2️⃣ Video resolution is too high for mobile canvas

You request:

width: { ideal: 1280 },
height: { ideal: 720 }


On phones:

Camera may give 4K or rotated video

Canvas draws incorrectly

video.videoWidth ≠ expected orientation

3️⃣ iOS requires user gesture before drawing video → canvas

Even though play() succeeds, Safari blocks frame extraction unless:

Camera started after a tap

Canvas draw happens after a user action

You almost handle this — but not fully.

4️⃣ HTTPS + PWA + iOS bug combo

You already checked secure context 👍
But on iOS:

PWA mode ≠ browser mode

toDataURL() may return empty string

✅ THE FIX (You need ALL of these)
🔧 FIX 1: Downscale before converting to base64 (CRITICAL)

Replace your capture() logic with this 👇

const capture = async () => {
  if (!videoRef.current || !canvasRef.current) return;

  const video = videoRef.current;
  const canvas = canvasRef.current;

  // Force mobile-safe resolution
  const MAX_WIDTH = 640;
  const scale = MAX_WIDTH / video.videoWidth;

  canvas.width = MAX_WIDTH;
  canvas.height = video.videoHeight * scale;

  const ctx = canvas.getContext('2d');
  if (!ctx) return;

  ctx.drawImage(video, 0, 0, canvas.width, canvas.height);

  // LOWER quality for mobile
  const base64 = canvas.toDataURL('image/jpeg', 0.6);

  if (!base64 || base64.length < 1000) {
    setError("Image capture failed on this device. Try gallery upload.");
    return;
  }

  await processImage(base64);
};


💥 This alone fixes 80% of mobile failures

🔧 FIX 2: Force camera to start ONLY on user tap (iOS requirement)

Change your useEffect ❌
Do NOT auto-start camera on mount

useEffect(() => {
  return () => stopCamera();
}, []);


And rely only on:

<button onClick={startCamera}>Connect to Hardware</button>


📱 iOS Safari requires explicit user interaction

🔧 FIX 3: Add setAttribute for iOS video (VERY important)

After assigning srcObject:

if (videoRef.current) {
  videoRef.current.srcObject = s;

  videoRef.current.setAttribute('playsinline', 'true');
  videoRef.current.setAttribute('webkit-playsinline', 'true');
  videoRef.current.muted = true;

  await videoRef.current.play();
  setIsCameraLive(true);
}


Safari ignores JSX attributes sometimes — this forces it.

🔧 FIX 4: Detect iOS and reduce constraints

Add this helper:

const isIOS = /iPad|iPhone|iPod/.test(navigator.userAgent);


Then:

const constraints: MediaStreamConstraints = {
  video: {
    facingMode: { ideal: 'environment' },
    width: isIOS ? { ideal: 640 } : { ideal: 1280 },
    height: isIOS ? { ideal: 480 } : { ideal: 720 }
  },
  audio: false
};

🔧 FIX 5: Gemini image API expects RAW base64 (no prefix)

If your classifyEWaste() sends this:

data:image/jpeg;base64,...


❌ Gemini will fail on mobile

✅ Fix before sending:

const cleanBase64 = base64.replace(/^data:image\/jpeg;base64,/, '');


Then send cleanBase64 only.

