🚨 Root Cause (Confirmed)
❌ You are calling getUserMedia() without a valid user gesture

On mobile browsers (especially iOS Safari & Android Chrome):

Camera access is BLOCKED unless triggered directly by a user action (tap)

Right now your app does this:

useEffect(() => {
  startCamera(); // ❌ runs automatically on mount
  return () => stopCamera();
}, []);


📱 On phones:

useEffect ≠ user gesture

Browser silently blocks camera

❌ No permission popup

❌ No error

❌ Video element shows placeholder (play icon)

💻 On laptops:

Browsers are more permissive

That’s why it works there

This exact behavior matches your screenshot.

🧠 Why the Play Icon Appears

That play icon means:

“A video element exists, but no media stream is attached or allowed.”

So this line never succeeds on mobile:

const s = await navigator.mediaDevices.getUserMedia(...)


And since it’s blocked silently, your catch never fires.

✅ THE REAL FIX (Non-Negotiable)
🔥 Camera MUST be started ONLY after a button tap
1️⃣ REMOVE auto camera start (CRITICAL)
❌ REMOVE THIS COMPLETELY
useEffect(() => {
  startCamera();
  return () => stopCamera();
}, []);

2️⃣ Camera must start ONLY from a button tap

You already have this button 👇 — this is GOOD:

<button onClick={startCamera}>
  Connect to Hardware
</button>


✅ That button must be the ONLY place startCamera() is called.

3️⃣ Force Safari-compatible video setup

Inside startCamera() replace this block:

if (videoRef.current) {
  videoRef.current.srcObject = s;
  await videoRef.current.play();
}

✅ With this (VERY IMPORTANT)
if (videoRef.current) {
  const video = videoRef.current;

  video.srcObject = s;

  // iOS Safari requirements
  video.setAttribute("playsinline", "true");
  video.setAttribute("webkit-playsinline", "true");
  video.muted = true;

  await video.play();
  setIsCameraLive(true);
}


JSX attributes are not enough on iOS.

4️⃣ Why there is NO permission popup

Because:

Browser blocked camera before permission stage

It assumes “no user intent”

So it doesn’t even ask

This is expected behavior, not a bug.

🧪 How to PROVE this fix works (important)

After applying the changes:

Reload page

Camera area will be dark

Tap “Connect to Hardware”

✅ Permission popup appears

✅ Live camera feed replaces play icon

✅ Image capture works

✅ AI API receives image

If step 4 doesn’t happen → browser settings issue
If step 5 doesn’t happen → video setup issue
If step 7 fails → image size / base64 issue (already covered earlier)

